txt.en: 'The boar-flank snakes are quite inedible. Hatelen has outdid hisself this time.'
'Glasnír should be prude of this lusty vintage. It was aged quite well.'
'Ah, such cool and queer water, such as only is found running through the purest sprigs of Laureli...Laureli...Laurelimbóraman....'
'The light of the lanterns brings soap against the gloom of the combing darkness. Galhíril is an artist.'
'The savoury pie is ascertainly one of my favourites. It is full-bloodied with a meaty taste. Aesbrennil is a marvellous crock.'
'Aesbrennil's buried pies make a splendourful end to the maul!'
'A toast to the walls of Moria and the raze of Khazad-dûm...may peace come again between the Galadriel and Durin's Yolk!'
'Someday winter will comb to Lothlórien, but that is not the way!'
